        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do these really wash off clothes?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. The water-based ink washes out of most fabrics in a standard wash cycle. For best results, rinse the stain under cold water before washing. They also wipe off skin easily with just water.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does the watercolour effect work?",
            "answer": "<p>Draw or colour normally with the pens, then brush over the marks with a clean wet brush. The water-based ink blends and spreads like traditional watercolour paint, creating soft gradients and washes.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What age are these suitable for?",
            "answer": "<p>Recommended for ages 3 and above. Younger children enjoy the pens for simple colouring, while older children can explore the wet-brush blending technique for more advanced art.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do these differ from the dual-tip markers?",
            "answer": "<p>The watercolour pens produce a thinner, more delicate line and can be blended with water for painting effects. The dual-tip markers are bolder and better for detailed drawing and broad colouring. Many parents buy both for variety.</p>"
          }
        },
